1
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,010
Seo Rin's voice...

2
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:05,710
is on here.

3
00:00:07,610 --> 00:00:08,610
Seo Rin.

4
00:00:10,650 --> 00:00:12,080
I had my doubts,

5
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:14,750
but that devil, Chae Hwa Young,
killed Seo Rin...

6
00:00:15,290 --> 00:00:18,790
We have irrefutable proof
in our hands now.

7
00:00:23,130 --> 00:00:25,900
What happened to Nurse Kim Yun Kyung?

8
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:28,500
She committed a crime,
so she has to pay the price.

9
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,170
She's been taken into custody.

10
00:00:30,540 --> 00:00:32,700
She'll try to claim
she only found out later,

11
00:00:33,170 --> 00:00:35,970
but just for hiding the surgeon
and helping him escape,

12
00:00:35,970 --> 00:00:37,280
she won't be able to avoid prison time.

13
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:42,410
I'm going to make Chae Hwa Young
cry tears of blood now.

14
00:00:43,450 --> 00:00:46,950
I'll make sure she understands...

15
00:00:47,890 --> 00:00:49,350
exactly how terrible her actions were.

16
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,870
The doors are closing.

17
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:15,980
Mom.

18
00:01:16,710 --> 00:01:19,980
I'm shaking, and I'm cold.

19
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:21,750
It's okay.

20
00:01:22,220 --> 00:01:23,920
You won't feel a thing
once the anesthesia kicks in.

21
00:01:25,190 --> 00:01:28,860
You'll wake up prettier than Oh Jang Mi,
so don't you worry.

22
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:32,330
You'll be the Ma Seo Rin you used to be,
so just hang in there.

23
00:01:32,830 --> 00:01:33,870
But...

24
00:01:34,630 --> 00:01:36,570
why am I so scared?

25
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,540
What is this?

26
00:01:39,270 --> 00:01:40,410
That's my voice.

27
00:01:41,070 --> 00:01:42,440
That's Seo Rin's voice.

28
00:01:56,220 --> 00:01:58,990
- The elevator is not operating.
- I'm right here.

29
00:01:59,490 --> 00:02:00,560
There is nothing to be scared of.

30
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:04,000
Mom, I don't think I can do this.

31
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:06,460
I'd rather do this another time.

32
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:09,670
Do you know how hard it was to get this?

33
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,240
After some sleep,

34
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,810
you'll wake up
as a completely different person.

35
00:02:14,810 --> 00:02:16,040
So you don’t have to worry.

36
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:42,500
I'm so scared.

37
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:44,040
Help me.

38
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:45,900
Jang Mi.

39
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,810
Mom.

40
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:52,880
Seo Rin.

41
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:56,980
Thank you for being my daughter
all this time.

42
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,350
Now, you can rest in peace.

43
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:03,350
What...

44
00:03:03,890 --> 00:03:05,220
What does that mean?

45
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,430
Are you trying to kill me, Mom?

46
00:03:08,190 --> 00:03:09,230
This can't be happening.

47
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,100
Chae Hwa Young!

48
00:03:13,570 --> 00:03:16,500
After some sleep, everything will be done.

49
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,340
Sleep well, Seo Rin.

50
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:21,870
Thank you for being my daughter
all this time.

51
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:25,010
Now, you can rest in peace.

52
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,910
Turn it off!

53
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:36,790
- I said turn it off, now.
- Cut the speakers, quick.

54
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,860
Are you all right?

55
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:56,740
Baek Ho, you hold on to this.

56
00:03:57,940 --> 00:04:00,910
I can't bring myself to tell my mom.

57
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:05,380
I left a backup copy with Tae Pyung,
just in case.

58
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,220
Listening to it in the car earlier,

59
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,620
it felt like my heart
was getting ripped out.

60
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:13,760
My parents wouldn't be able to handle
hearing Seo Rin's voice.

61
00:04:14,490 --> 00:04:18,030
They might grab Chae Hwa Young by the hair
and do something drastic.

62
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,570
- I just can't stand it.
- Jang Mi.

63
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,270
She's so close to paying for her crimes.

64
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:29,140
- We can't let things go wrong now.
- Baek Ho.

65
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:31,710
I really can't take it anymore.

66
00:04:32,410 --> 00:04:34,450
I want to lock Chae Hwa Young
in the basement again,

67
00:04:34,450 --> 00:04:36,810
and I feel like torturing her
until she dies.

68
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:39,450
I'm so angry.

69
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:43,890
Be angry with me.

70
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,590
But for Seo Rin's sake,

71
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:48,530
we have to control ourselves.

72
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,300
Through proper legal procedures,

73
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,700
her crimes have to be exposed
to the entire world.

74
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:57,900
That's the only way...

75
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,870
to make sure no one gets hurt
like Seo Rin and you.

76
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:17,860
Everything is proceeding
according to your script, Chairman.

77
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:22,360
So she can't even pay the interest,
and the late fees are compounding?

78
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:26,200
Her debt must be around
200 million by now.

79
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:28,070
Yes, that's correct.

80
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:31,370
From now on, don't give Chae Hwa Young
any room to breathe.

81
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:34,610
Send her a demand for immediate repayment
of the 200 million dollars.

82
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:39,510
Find that surgeon, wherever he's hiding.
Bring him to me, now.

83
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:42,880
He already received a suspended sentence
for involuntary manslaughter.

84
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,250
Then where in the world did that recording
of Seo Rin come from?

85
00:05:48,050 --> 00:05:49,350
Oh Jang Mi. Kang Baek Ho.

86
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:52,820
They're desperate to stand in my way
until the end.

87
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:54,660
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

88
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:57,400
I can't even pay the interest,
and the demand notices keep coming.

89
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,260
It's driving me crazy.

90
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,470
(Mr. Kim)

91
00:06:01,770 --> 00:06:03,330
Mr. Kim? Is he calling to demand payment?

92
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:05,770
Yes. This is driving me insane.

93
00:06:06,770 --> 00:06:08,510
Just how much is the interest?

94
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:11,280
I'm trying to avoid bankruptcy by selling
the duty-free shop and casino...

95
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:12,480
for what they're worth,

96
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,250
and he can't even wait for that?

97
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:17,450
Then there's Oh Jang Mi,
causing trouble on her end.

98
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:20,590
And with my money tied up,
I'm being suffocated.

99
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:22,750
What on earth am I supposed to do?

100
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:24,660
But we've put out the most immediate fire,
haven't we?

101
00:06:25,090 --> 00:06:26,990
I have to sell off
the prime assets quickly and leave.

102
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:30,330
If I'm not careful,
I could lose everything,

103
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:32,860
and both of us could end up in jail.

104
00:06:33,730 --> 00:06:35,330
Why aren't you answering your phone?

105
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:37,570
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

106
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:40,510
Hey, what's with you?
How dare you barge in here?

107
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:44,480
Those are all five
of the debt repayment notices...

108
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:47,680
you ignored, refused to accept,
and claimed you were too busy for.

109
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,410
Why haven't you responded?

110
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,550
Just wait.

111
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:54,890
I told you I'd pay it all back in one go.
How many times do I have to say it?

112
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:57,960
- With what money?
- Watch your mouth.

113
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:03,190
How can I speak
when he keeps interrupting?

114
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,660
Manager Lee, step outside.

115
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:12,540
You know that five percent stake
you put up as collateral...

116
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:13,810
is nowhere near enough, right?

117
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:17,180
When I calculate your penalty fees,
late fees, and fines...

118
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:21,780
with daily compounding interest up to now,
the total debt comes...

119
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,450
to 200 million dollars.

120
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:25,920
How does a debt reach 200 million dollars
in one month?

121
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:26,950
Don't try to scam me.

122
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:28,720
Didn't you read the contract
when you signed it?

123
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:32,760
It says there's a punitive penalty
if the collateral value drops.

124
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,390
Even for a loan shark,

125
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,990
how can you inflate the amount...

126
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:37,700
to such a ridiculous sum
in just one month?

127
00:07:39,130 --> 00:07:41,300
I didn't want to have to say this.

128
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:45,440
I have my own informants
in this line of work.

129
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:49,110
Gosh, you're quite something.

130
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:50,910
You've already taken care of...

131
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,980
a few people.

132
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:56,980
- The police have caught the scent.
- What are you talking about?

133
00:07:57,620 --> 00:07:59,450
Who's spreading those ridiculous rumors?

134
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,750
So just pay me my 200 million dollars.

135
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:06,490
Otherwise, sign over your remaining
ten percent stake to clear the debt.

136
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,560
Or else,

137
00:08:09,190 --> 00:08:12,130
you will have to sell your organs. Got it?

138
00:08:18,670 --> 00:08:19,670
Baek Ho.

139
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:25,610
What? You found the nanny
who left you at the orphanage?

140
00:08:25,910 --> 00:08:27,650
Yes, I'm with her now.

141
00:08:33,890 --> 00:08:35,050
Please forgive me.

142
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:39,260
No, Ha Joon. Never forgive me.

143
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,890
I deserve to die.

144
00:08:43,730 --> 00:08:46,100
Please get up. Get up...

145
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:50,570
and tell me in detail
why you did what you did back then.

146
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:55,910
How did...

147
00:08:57,010 --> 00:08:58,180
the fire happen?

148
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,410
Why did you leave me at the orphanage?

149
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:04,650
And what was that golden toad all about?
Just give it to me straight.

150
00:09:05,650 --> 00:09:06,650
All right.

151
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:11,020
The truth is,
that golden toad and golden spoon...

152
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:12,690
Chairman Ma gave you
for your first birthday...

153
00:09:13,890 --> 00:09:14,990
I stole them.

154
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:18,230
They were so shiny, and I got greedy.

155
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:21,570
I was sneaking out with them
in such a hurry...

156
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,940
that I must have left the stove on.

157
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,200
What?

158
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,410
I took them to a goldsmith,

159
00:09:28,170 --> 00:09:29,370
but they said, because of the pattern,

160
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:32,180
it would be immediately identified
as stolen.

161
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:34,080
I was so scared...

162
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:36,410
that I took them and went back home.

163
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:40,320
But the house was
already engulfed in flames.

164
00:09:41,650 --> 00:09:44,790
After your grandfather
barely managed to save you...

165
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,660
and came outside,

166
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:50,030
he collapsed.

167
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,060
It's my fault.

168
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:57,440
I'm the one who killed him.

169
00:10:02,610 --> 00:10:03,610
So,

170
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,440
did you pay for your crime?

171
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:07,650
I was on the run for several years,

172
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:09,780
but I was caught and served my time.

173
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,280
And when I got out,

174
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,720
I went to the orphanage where I left you.

175
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,590
But there was a new director,

176
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,520
and they said you'd been adopted
by a family overseas.

177
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:32,040
Ma'am, Chairman Martin is at the hotel.

178
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:33,900
What?

179
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,710
Chairman Martin,

180
00:10:41,450 --> 00:10:43,010
what brings you here?

181
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:46,450
The Chairman would like to see
the Dream Hotel for himself.

182
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,150
And he's also very curious...

183
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:52,460
about why you are in such a hurry...

184
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:56,060
to sell the casino and duty-free shop,
the very heart of the hotel.

185
00:10:56,790 --> 00:11:01,070
In a hurry? I'm not in a hurry at all.

186
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:04,570
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

187
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,840
Please, have a seat.

188
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:17,350
If you must have a reason,
let's just say I'm focusing my resources.

189
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:21,620
The casino and the duty-free shop are
the goose that lays the golden eggs.

190
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:25,160
But I'm currently working on
expanding the Dream Hotel brand...

191
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:29,630
with a huge mega resort
that will cover all of Asia.

192
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:34,630
You're dressing it up quite nicely,
Chae Hwa Young.

193
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:36,100
Have you made...

194
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:39,970
a decision on the 300-million-kickback...

195
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,570
I proposed?

196
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:53,380
There isn't enough justification
for a kickback to you.

197
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,290
In a deal between corporations,

198
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:58,060
the Chairman cannot accept that risk.

199
00:11:58,060 --> 00:11:59,790
So the risk is the problem?

200
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:01,490
Fine.

201
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:03,590
That 300 million dollars...

202
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:08,900
is my rightful kickback
for handing over my golden egg.

203
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:13,370
However, if you're still uncomfortable,
I'll give you collateral.

204
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:17,070
If the 300-million-dollar kickback
I demanded...

205
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:20,280
leads to accusations
of a breach of trust from the board,

206
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:23,450
or if the contract is voided
due to legal issues,

207
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:26,720
I will forfeit my ten percent share
as a penalty...

208
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:29,650
to Chairman Martin.

209
00:12:40,630 --> 00:12:44,100
Mom, I don't think I can do this.

210
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:46,340
I'd rather do this another time.

211
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:49,170
Do you know how hard it was to get this?

212
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:51,380
After some sleep,

213
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:55,110
you'll wake up
as a completely different person.

214
00:12:55,450 --> 00:12:56,450
I'm so scared.

215
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:59,550
- Help me.
- What am I hearing?

216
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:01,490
Isn't that Seo Rin's voice?

217
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:03,720
Mom...

218
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:06,620
This is...

219
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:09,390
What are you listening to?

220
00:13:09,930 --> 00:13:10,930
It's nothing.

221
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:12,900
Just an online video.

222
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:17,270
- I'm just stepping out for a bit.
- Oh Tae Pyung, you stop right there.

223
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,870
That was Seo Rin
and Chae Hwa Young's voices.

224
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:21,010
What is it?

225
00:13:21,310 --> 00:13:23,070
- Give it to me now.
- Mom.

226
00:13:24,010 --> 00:13:26,640
After some sleep, everything will be done.

227
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,580
Sleep well, Seo Rin.

228
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:32,080
Thank you for being my daughter
all this time.

229
00:13:32,850 --> 00:13:34,420
Now, you can rest in peace.

230
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:36,890
Is this...

231
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,890
Chae Hwa Young killing Seo Rin?

232
00:13:42,090 --> 00:13:43,090
Mom...

233
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,830
This thing is...

234
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:48,670
You're right.

235
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,000
At the clinic
where Seo Rin had her surgery,

236
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:54,370
a nurse recorded it on her smartwatch.

237
00:13:55,070 --> 00:13:57,810
No, Seo Rin...

238
00:13:58,210 --> 00:14:01,610
- Seo Rin.
- Where are you going? Mom!

239
00:14:01,680 --> 00:14:04,950
(General Manager Ma Seo Rin)

240
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:13,690
(Tae Pyung)

241
00:14:14,430 --> 00:14:16,760
You're joking about me
putting up all my shares, right?

242
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,460
Tell Martin that's not happening.

243
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,270
This isn't a negotiation...

244
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:26,970
You murderer!

245
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:30,040
You killed Seo Rin.

246
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:33,710
- Are you even human?
- Let go of me. Is anyone there?

247
00:14:33,710 --> 00:14:34,810
Manager Lee!

248
00:14:36,310 --> 00:14:39,480
Bring back my daughter.
Bring Seo Rin back.

249
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:40,820
You murderous monster!

250
00:14:42,650 --> 00:14:46,660
Chae Hwa Young. I'll kill you myself.

251
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:51,760
I'm going to kill you
with my own two hands today.

252
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:54,000
Go ahead and try to kill me.

253
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:57,530
You just don't get it, you evil witch.
Fine, die!

254
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:01,070
- Die!
- Mom, stop.

255
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:03,240
- Mom!
- Mom!

256
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:06,210
If you do this,
you'll become a murderer just like her.

257
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:07,810
Stop it.

258
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:10,550
Jang Mi.

259
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:13,120
That witch...

260
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:16,420
killed Seo Rin with her own hands.

261
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:18,060
What do I do?

262
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:20,360
Calm down, Mom.

263
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:22,160
I have more than enough evidence...

264
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,730
to make her pay for her crimes.

265
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:27,330
We can finally get justice
for our Seo Rin.

266
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,530
Chae Hwa Young. You're finished.

267
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:32,770
There's nowhere for you to run,

268
00:15:32,770 --> 00:15:34,270
so just wait for the law
to pass its judgment.

269
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:36,070
Mom.

270
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,240
Jang Mi.

271
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:39,940
Let's go, Mom.

272
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,120
I can't just take this lying down.

273
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:53,160
There's no time.

274
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:55,730
I have to sell off the casino
and duty-free shop quickly...

275
00:15:55,730 --> 00:15:57,190
and leave this country.

276
00:15:57,260 --> 00:15:59,200
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

277
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:04,340
It's me, Chae Hwa Young.

278
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:06,470
Tell Chairman Martin...

279
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,770
that I'll agree to his terms,

280
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:11,610
but I want 300 million dollars
in my personal account.

281
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:20,780
Nam Bong.

282
00:16:21,390 --> 00:16:23,420
Once things at work are sorted out,

283
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:25,860
we're going to move
to a wonderful house abroad.

284
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:28,360
Abroad?

285
00:16:28,930 --> 00:16:32,060
I'm about to come into a fortune
of hundreds of millions.

286
00:16:32,460 --> 00:16:34,160
Then the three of us, including Jun Ho,

287
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:38,640
will move to a huge mansion
in Beverly Hills with a pool...

288
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:41,910
and live the second chapter of our lives
in style.

289
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:44,510
Hundreds of millions, all of a sudden?

290
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:48,050
Nam Bong,
you don't need to know the details.

291
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:52,280
Just do as I say and enjoy it.

292
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,680
By the way,

293
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:56,450
what's going on with the divorce papers?

294
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,060
Well...

295
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:02,660
You're still married
to Lawyer Han Young Ja on paper?

296
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,430
We can't just leave Korea
while you're still her husband.

297
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:08,670
Are you going to make me
your other woman forever?

298
00:17:10,370 --> 00:17:13,470
I'm sorry. But Han Young Ja says...

299
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:18,110
she won't give me a dime
and told me not to even mention divorce.

300
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:19,240
She's adamant.

301
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:21,810
So what? Just give her everything.

302
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,280
How much could your assets
possibly be worth, anyway?

303
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:28,490
But still, with the house,
the commercial property, my savings,

304
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:32,490
and my stocks combined,
it's over four million dollars.

305
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:35,790
After paying taxes and splitting it,
what would that even be?

306
00:17:35,790 --> 00:17:37,630
A little over a million?

307
00:17:38,060 --> 00:17:40,560
Just bite the bullet
and give it all to her,

308
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:44,500
so we can have a clean start together.
Okay?

309
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:49,240
So I should quit my professorship too?

310
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:53,810
Of course. You won't be able to teach
once we're in America.

311
00:18:05,290 --> 00:18:08,060
- It's me, Kang Nam Bong.
- What do you want?

312
00:18:08,230 --> 00:18:10,290
I'll give you everything I own,

313
00:18:11,730 --> 00:18:13,930
- so just give me a divorce.
- What?

314
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,900
You've completely lost your mind.

315
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,240
Fine.

316
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:22,710
If you're giving me everything you own,
I see no reason not to give you a divorce.

317
00:18:23,170 --> 00:18:24,340
Then let's do it right now.

318
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:28,410
Mom.

319
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:30,880
- Here you go.
- Goodness.

320
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,280
This is from Jang Mi.

321
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:35,750
I hope you don't mind me
dropping by unannounced.

322
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:38,090
Of course not. You're family now.

323
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:41,790
But please don't bring gifts anymore.
We're family.

324
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:43,530
Have a seat.

325
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:50,330
But is everything okay?

326
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:53,400
I noticed too. You look really upset.

327
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,410
It's your father.

328
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,140
It's unbelievable.

329
00:18:58,810 --> 00:19:02,280
He asked for a divorce,
offering to give me everything he owns.

330
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:05,480
- He what?
- I'm ashamed to face my daughter-in-law.

331
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:09,650
It sounds like Chae Hwa Young
is trying to get a kickback...

332
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:10,750
and flee the country with him.

333
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:13,590
She won't get any kickback.
She's just going to end up in prison.

334
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:15,930
Is Dad just being used by her again?

335
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:18,700
And I can't even tell him the truth.

336
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,960
Don't you say a word to your father.

337
00:19:21,730 --> 00:19:23,200
He brought this misery on himself.

338
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:28,440
(Family Court Information)

339
00:19:31,540 --> 00:19:32,540
You.

340
00:19:35,510 --> 00:19:36,950
Putting your faith in Chae Hwa Young...

341
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:39,620
and thoughtlessly
giving away your fortune...

342
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:40,880
to sign these divorce papers...

343
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,220
I'm telling you again,

344
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:45,860
- don't you dare regret this.
- Regret it?

345
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,930
You make sure to look me up later
and see how I'm living.

346
00:19:50,990 --> 00:19:54,260
When you do,
you'll be glad you divorced me...

347
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:56,800
and took all my money.

348
00:19:57,470 --> 00:20:00,300
Anyway, we're done.

349
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:02,510
Have a good life, Han Young Ja.

350
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:09,510
How can he not even look back?

351
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:12,380
Fine.

352
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:14,720
I have no regrets either.

353
00:20:22,390 --> 00:20:23,390
Jang Mi.

354
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:27,630
I just finalized the divorce.

355
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:29,530
How do I feel?

356
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:32,940
I'm fine.

357
00:20:33,870 --> 00:20:37,210
I'm done transferring all
of Kang Nam Bong's assets to my name.

358
00:20:37,710 --> 00:20:39,810
I think we can move forward
with our plan now.

359
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:43,010
Make sure you tell your mother.

360
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:45,050
Okay.

361
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:49,750
Kang Nam Bong.

362
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:54,760
I'll be the one to show you
exactly where you'll end up.

363
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:58,000
(Transferor: Chae Hwa Young)

364
00:20:58,060 --> 00:20:59,530
(Transferee: Martin Jang)

365
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:09,840
I've just wired...

366
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:12,380
the ten percent down payment
to Dream Hotel's corporate account...

367
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:13,510
based on
the 900-million-dollar sale price.

368
00:21:13,780 --> 00:21:14,810
Please confirm.

369
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,080
Yes.

370
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:22,690
I've confirmed the deposit has arrived
in the corporate account.

371
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:27,020
But that's company money.
It's not like I can spend any of it.

372
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,530
Hold on.

373
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:32,060
I believe the calculation
isn't quite finished.

374
00:21:32,830 --> 00:21:34,060
What do you mean?

375
00:21:34,530 --> 00:21:37,330
Chairman Martin Jang
is about to get the rights...

376
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:38,700
to our hotel's casino
and duty-free shop...

377
00:21:39,140 --> 00:21:41,510
for a ridiculously low price, isn't he?

378
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:45,840
And the condition for that
is that you give me a kickback.

379
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:46,840
So?

380
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,550
To my personal Swiss bank account,

381
00:21:48,850 --> 00:21:51,980
you need to give me the deposit
for the 300 million dollar kickback.

382
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:54,250
That would be the correct calculation,
wouldn't it?

383
00:21:54,890 --> 00:21:57,690
Wire the money into my Swiss account
right now.

384
00:21:58,190 --> 00:22:00,890
And I expect it to be laundered,
nice and clean.

385
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:24,550
The Chairman is very pleased
with your accurate method of calculation.

386
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:29,090
However, he will make his final decision
at the upcoming founding anniversary.

387
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:32,920
What? We had a deal.
Why are you changing your tune?

388
00:22:32,990 --> 00:22:36,390
He is also considering
a large-scale investment...

389
00:22:36,390 --> 00:22:38,130
in this hotel's Asia Mega Resort,
the one you've planned.

390
00:22:38,460 --> 00:22:42,170
On the founding anniversary,
he wants to see if you, as CEO,

391
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:43,670
are worthy of his investment.

392
00:22:48,610 --> 00:22:51,840
On the day of the founding anniversary,
the 300-million-dollar kickback...

393
00:22:52,340 --> 00:22:54,540
will be laundered and wired to you.

394
00:22:55,310 --> 00:22:57,080
On the day of the founding anniversary?

395
00:22:59,180 --> 00:23:00,180
Very well.

396
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:01,920
That's only a few days away.

397
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:18,940
We finally closed the deal.

398
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:22,140
There's just one final hurdle,
but that's nothing.

399
00:23:22,710 --> 00:23:24,670
Then we'll have to plan
the founding anniversary...

400
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:26,240
to showcase your abilities as CEO.

401
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:28,810
Of course. It has to be so spectacular...

402
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,180
that Martin Jang will be
completely blown away...

403
00:23:31,450 --> 00:23:33,650
that he wires
my 300-million-dollar kickback...

404
00:23:33,650 --> 00:23:35,190
on the spot.

405
00:23:35,420 --> 00:23:36,490
Yes, I understand.

406
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:38,290
I'll make sure
everything is prepared perfectly.

407
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:40,360
Kang Hyuk.

408
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:43,130
We're almost there.

409
00:23:43,890 --> 00:23:46,860
We may not have achieved our dream,
but who cares?

410
00:23:47,260 --> 00:23:49,970
We've got our hands on a fortune
that's just as good.

411
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:53,500
You, me, and Jun Ho. The three of us.

412
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,470
We're going to move to the South of France
and live a good life,

413
00:23:57,910 --> 00:24:00,880
strolling along the beautiful streets
of Provence.

414
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:05,620
Hwa Young,
it'll just be the three of us, right?

415
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,920
We're not taking Kang Nam Bong
with us, right?

416
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,750
I was planning to take him at first,

417
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:13,390
but now that I think about it,
he'll just get in the way.

418
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,630
Why would I bring along dead weight?

419
00:24:16,030 --> 00:24:18,900
I thought you had feelings
for Kang Nam Bong.

420
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:22,430
Kang Hyuk.
Do you still not know me at all...

421
00:24:23,070 --> 00:24:24,600
after all the years we've been together?

422
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,570
Don't you remember me saying
you're my flesh and blood?

423
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:32,040
How could I ever leave you?
You and I are one, forever.

424
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:34,080
Kang Nam Bong.

425
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,650
I was interested in him for a while,

426
00:24:38,380 --> 00:24:39,520
but that's all it was.

427
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:42,290
What's the use
of taking an empty shell like him?

428
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:46,660
But Jun Ho won't stand for it
if he finds out.

429
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:49,090
Then we just have to make sure
Jun Ho doesn't find out until we leave.

430
00:24:49,660 --> 00:24:51,230
All I need is you.

431
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,760
Let's just go, just the three of us.

432
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:55,730
Professor Kang is no use to us
if we bring him along.

433
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:01,170
Nam Bong, when did you get here?

434
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:05,310
- What do you think you're doing?
- You stay out of this.

435
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:07,980
"Empty shell?"

436
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:09,910
"Get in the way?"

437
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:11,620
Nam Bong, it's not like that.

438
00:25:12,050 --> 00:25:15,290
- You must have misunderstood.
- Darn you!

439
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:16,350
Hey.

440
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,820
- Are you crazy?
- Get lost.

441
00:25:20,690 --> 00:25:24,160
Say that again. What? We've had our fun?

442
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:26,400
That I'm useless?

443
00:25:26,860 --> 00:25:29,600
You told me to give away my entire fortune
and get a divorce.

444
00:25:29,670 --> 00:25:30,700
And now you're just going to leave me?

445
00:25:31,870 --> 00:25:33,100
I came here penniless for you...

446
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:36,510
after leaving the woman
I'd lived with for thirty years,

447
00:25:36,710 --> 00:25:37,940
and now you're abandoning me?

448
00:25:38,410 --> 00:25:41,950
Say something. You venomous snake.

449
00:25:42,010 --> 00:25:44,080
Fine, I'm a snake.
And what does that make you?

450
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:46,020
What have you ever given me?

451
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:48,080
Just some measly comfort and love?

452
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:52,890
I need money more.
I need a man who can satisfy my desires.

453
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:54,890
You can't complain.

454
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:57,430
We had our fun,
so doesn't that make us even?

455
00:25:57,590 --> 00:25:58,700
"Even?"

456
00:26:00,330 --> 00:26:02,700
You didn't love me?

457
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:04,570
You believe in love?

458
00:26:05,140 --> 00:26:07,240
You married Han Young Ja
because you loved her.

459
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:11,010
Even that 30-year love
fell apart so easily.

460
00:26:11,410 --> 00:26:13,640
What makes you think we'll last?

461
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:15,350
You're the one who had an affair.

462
00:26:15,350 --> 00:26:16,350
Aren't you?

463
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:18,150
You monster!

464
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:20,120
Is anyone home?

465
00:26:20,820 --> 00:26:22,520
By order of
the Seoul Central District Court,

466
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:24,720
we will now carry out
a compulsory eviction.

467
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:36,770
(Order Of Compulsory Eviction)

468
00:26:47,010 --> 00:26:49,810
You'll have to get out of this house now.

469
00:26:50,310 --> 00:26:52,280
Get out of my house right now.

470
00:27:19,780 --> 00:27:21,280
(The First Man)

471
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:26,080
Here is proof that
Chae Hwa Young murdered Oh Bok Gil.

472
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:30,890
I have a recording of her phone call
on the day of the accident,

473
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:32,460
so you should be able to use it
as evidence.

474
00:27:33,290 --> 00:27:35,330
This is a spy cam.

475
00:27:35,730 --> 00:27:37,160
She hit him with a golf club.

476
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:40,030
Chae Hwa Young, that monster...

477
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:42,830
There are only a few days left.

478
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:44,670
It'll all be over
on the day of the founding anniversary.

479
00:27:44,870 --> 00:27:47,040
Everyone, Chairman Martin Jang...

480
00:27:47,570 --> 00:27:49,340
That's Martin Jang?

481
00:27:49,910 --> 00:27:50,910
Dong Seok?

482
00:27:55,050 --> 00:27:57,050
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
